inscope.li:
the following set theory relationships:


complement;

equivalence;

intersection;

power set;

proper subset;

subset;

union.

outscope.li:
entities and relationships specific to continuous sets.

All the entities and relationships within this part of ISO 10303 are equally valid for discrete and continuous sets.

Entities and relationships for continuous sets can be created in anntotated EXPRESS schemas that use or specialize entities in this part of ISO 10303, as follows:


discrete_class_by_intension and continuous_set can be disjoint subtypes of ;

open_set and closed_set can be disjoint subtypes of continuous_set;

closure can be the relationship between an open_set and the closed_set that is its boundary.

schema.introduction:
The set_theory_schema specifies the following relationships between classes:


complement;

intersection;

power set;

proper subset;

same membership (that is, set equality); 

subset;

union.
